Here's how to implement this in .NET MAUI Shell:

## 1. Override `OnBackButtonPressed` on your page

```csharp
public partial class EditProductPage : ContentPage
{
    private bool _hasUnsavedChanges;

    protected override bool OnBackButtonPressed()
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            // Fire-and-forget the async confirmation
            MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread(async () =>
            {
                bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
                    "Unsaved Changes",
                    "You have unsaved changes. Discard and go back?",
                    "Discard", "Stay");

                if (leave)
                    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
            });

            return true; // cancel the default navigation
        }

        return false; // allow normal back
    }
}
```

> `OnBackButtonPressed` handles the **hardware/OS back button** (Android back gesture, etc.). Return `true` to cancel navigation.

## 2. Handle the Shell back-button in the toolbar

Hide the default back arrow and add a custom "Cancel" button:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.EditProductPage"
             Shell.BackButtonBehavior="{x:Null}">

    <Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
        <BackButtonBehavior
            TextOverride="Cancel"
            IconOverride=""
            Command="{Binding CancelCommand}" />
    </Shell.BackButtonBehavior>

    <!-- page content -->
</ContentPage>
```

## 3. ViewModel command with confirmation

```csharp
[RelayCommand]
private async Task Cancel()
{
    if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
    {
        bool leave = await Shell.Current.DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "You have unsaved changes. Discard and go back?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (!leave) return; // stay on page
    }

    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
}
```

## Key points

| Scenario | Mechanism |
|----------|-----------|
| Android/hardware back | `OnBackButtonPressed()` → return `true` to block |
| Shell toolbar back | `BackButtonBehavior` with custom `Command` |
| Swipe-back (iOS) | Not interceptable by Shell — consider disabling via platform code if critical |

To disable iOS swipe-back, add this in your page's handler:

```csharp
#if IOS
protected override void OnAppearing()
{
    base.OnAppearing();
    var navController = Platform.GetCurrentUIViewController()
        ?.NavigationController;
    if (navController != null)
        navController.InteractivePopGestureRecognizer.Enabled = false;
}
#endif
```

This gives you full control over back navigation with an unsaved-changes guard.
